Russian Equity Movers: Acron, Magnitogorsk, Transneft in Moscow

-- B y   S t e p h e n   K i r k l a n d
-- 
2011-08-26T15:48:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/russian-movers-eurasia-drilling-petropavlovsk-rosneft.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  rose 1.1
percent to 1,458.84 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow, leaving
the gauge up 1.4 percent this week. The dollar-denominated RTS
Index added 0.8 percent to 1,596.17.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Acron (AKRN RX), a Russian fertilizer producer, rose to
the highest in more than three weeks after reporting profit more
than doubled in the first half. The stock advanced 1.6 percent
to 1,340.5 rubles, the highest since Aug. 3.  OAO Magnitogorsk Iron & Steel (MAGN RX), Russian
billionaire Victor Rashnikov’s steelmaker, fell for a seventh
day in its longest losing streak since 2008 after reporting
profit slumped 81 percent in the second quarter. The shares
declined 2.1 percent to 16.65 rubles.  OAO Polymetal (PMTL RX), a Russian silver and gold
producer, gained for the first time in three days, jumping 1.9
percent to 603.9 rubles. Gold gained $29, or 1.6 percent, to
$1,792.20 at 10:16 a.m. on the Comex in  New York .  OAO Transneft (TRNFP RX),  Russia ’s oil pipeline operator,
rose for a third day, advancing 4 percent to 38,266 rubles. The
Federal Tariff Service will review proposed increases in pumping
rates of an average 2.8 percent on Sept. 1 and 5 percent from
Nov. 1 at a meeting on Aug. 31, Denis Volkov, the regulator’s
head of oil and gas regulation, said by phone today. The
increase will help to pay off expansion costs and ward off
“terrorists” and “thieves,” Igor Dyomin, a company
spokesman, said by telephone today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Kirkland in London at 
